Her children by Germanicus were Nero, Drusus, Caligula (emperor), Agrippina (mother of Nero, the emperor), Drusilla, J ulia. —Augustae . . . odiis). Livia, the second wife of Augustus and mother of Tiberius and Drusus (the elder), was adopted into the Julian family under the name of Augusta (sec. 14); hence she was the grandmother (aviae) of Germanicus, who was the son of her son Drusus.
